cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CYBER, cs.CL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on identifying socially minded users on Twitter and analysing their network and content-based metrics. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also a likely category as the paper deals with social media platforms and online activism. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper describes a pipeline for harvesting and analysing Twitter data. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is relevant as the paper deals with user profiling and privacy concerns on social media platforms. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still relevant as the paper deals with natural language processing and text analysis of Twitter data.
